column315: Betting on the highest number or 6. I didn't always use that strategy because I didn't think about it
After the 4th round, I decided to choose 6 every time because it's the most amount of money, and I had rolled it a couple of times.
I don't think there is a strategy for rolling dice.
No strategy - but I took longer to make my decision after i had won some coins.
Picked randomly
random bets
I chose particulars until the die landed on that number, at which point I then chose a different number.
Initially, I just chose random numbers for the bets. However, as I kept getting high numbers, I decided to use a different strategy in which I picked a random number between 4 and 6.
No, I knew that there was a 1/6 chance for ever number every roll so I just chose a number.
Based off of previous experience with dice rolling, I tended to roll lower numbers and so those were the numbers I chose
I wanted to bet equally across the six possible numbers in order to maximize my chances of winning.
I figured that I should just choose a high number, so that if I happened to match my bet, I would receive a high amount of quarters. Maybe I should have chosen 6, but I chose 5 arbitrarily.
First, choosing 4 and then choosing at random after that.
Considering how many times a number came up before. No
Best to choose 6- equal likelihood for all bets, but 6 gives most return

Because each number has the same chance of being chosen, the obvious choice is to select the higher number. However, choosing 6 each time would not be the most likely outcome. So I chose between 4, 5, and 6.

I picked randomly as each number should have equal chance of winning; in the beginning I ocnsidered choosing one number and sticking to ti but then decided it didn't matter as each number should have the same chance of winning each round. I stayed with five and one other number for a while.
just picked a random number
Should have stuck to the same number. But yes, I chose different numbers
chose at random
I chose random numbers until round 6-7.
Pick 6 every time, as that provides the highest payout while having an equal probability to the other possibilities
always choose 2
There is an equal probability of rolling every number so choose 6 each time
Choosing 6 everytime would have been the best strategy because then you would receive the most quarters if you won
Choose the number that pays most. Yes.
Assuming all sides are equally likely, choose the one that pays out the best.

I guess it might've worked to bet on the same number each time, but I didn't do that. I just tried to vary my bets, then remembered at the end that I had been shying away from 1 and 6, so bet on those.
No, because all numbers have the same chance, you would place the maximum bet each round.
Go with six, every time
I just did it at random because I couldn't figure out a strategy, although choosing 6 each time probably would've been the best
random numbers each time because each roll is an independent event
I chose the same number for each round. I don't think that with a fair die, there is a "best" strategy.
I started and ended choosing 6 because it awarded the most if I won, but I didn't really trust that the dice were fair.
None./ No.
I don't think there is a strategy. I stuck with the same strategy.
bet on a higher number, since each number is euqally likely to be rolled. I used the same strategy for each round
I do not think there is a best strategy to win this game.
I chose the same number in all rounds
no
No
Staying on one number until you get it then switching to the number that was least rolled. I chose a random number that was different from the test roll.
Not really. I just picked random numbers.
The best strategy is probably to chose numbers that have not been rolled often.  I did not really use any strategy.
It's all random.
Bet six every time, 1/6 chance for any of the numbers so might as well choose the highest
LOWER OF HIGHER
Choose numbers above 3. Used this strategy for the majority of my guesses.
sticking to the same number
Go for the highest number since all the numbers had an equal chance of being rolled. That would theoretically result in the most money gained.
Guessing the same number every time.  Yes
I don't believe there is a "best" strategy, it's a game of luck.
I picked pretty randomly since i based it mostly on my favorite numbers
The best strategy is to always bet on six, increasing the expected value of the number of quarters you get.

Since 6 has, statistically, the same chance of any number and selecting 6 will guarantee you all of the quarters from that round, it would make sense to keep guessing 6. I adhered to this strategy for each round.
don't know
For the most part I stuck with my favorite number
Choosing the number that the die landing on multiple times
I don't really think there is much of a strategy
Choose 6 all the time for all rounds.
No, all the numbers had the same amount of chance, so I just chose the highest
If the dice is a 6, then you get the most reward. And since the dice is fair, it gives you the best chances
I tried to be consistent, and I wanted to choose a high enough payment for it to be worth it.
Pick 6 every time
No I tried to use the same number, since each outcome has the same chance of winning.
Just picked a random number every time
Strategies are useless, as the probability is the same every time.
no real strategy; 4,5,6 seemed to be popping up more frequently so i guessed those numbers more frequently
I found no strategy useful.
Staying with the same roll every time
I do not think there is a best strategy.Thus, after a few rolls, I just bet on the same number.
choose randomly; if i didn't get one number, sometimes i tried it again

To try and win the highest number, you pick one (3 or above if possible) that has not been seen before or has been seen the least, and stick with it until it shows up, then move to the next least seen and so on.
i tried to pick a number and stick with it until i rolled it
I based my choices on the number of times I kept rolling certain numbers, i.e. I rolled "5" multiple times.
I chose the same two numbers for the most part, such as 3 and 4.
Pick the highest number because each face has an equal probability; used the same strategy throughout
Pick six every time, you have the same chance at being right as with any other number but you get more quarters if you are. I used this strategy every round.
Choose the same number for every round

I would say for someone that has never rolled a die before, probably sticking to the same number would be best. Depending on how someone rolls the die though, the way they throw the die could be affecting what number they get, so the strategy might change depending on how they throw the die.
I always chose 6 because if I rolled a 6 I would keep all of my quarters.
I used a brain teasing method to pick the number before I win
I did. I did 4 the last couple of times because I was hoping for a high number and it didnt get rolled in a while.
I selected the same number for most of the rounds thinking it was bound to come up at some point - and it did - twice.
I chose six because I believe every number had an equal chance so I might as well maximize my payoff for each round.
Keep betting for 6
Pick the highest number, last couple of rounds randomly picked numbers.
Bet the same number each roll. I bet a different number each time.
I think the best strategy is to choose 6 because there is an even chance that it will be any of the 6 numbers and if if is 6, you can keep the most quarters
I think randomly choosing is the best strategy.  I randomly chose in all rounds.

I chose 6 every round because if the die is fair i have an equal chance of winning on any given number - then the expected return on each roll betting 6 is $0.25 whereas the expected return betting 1 is only 1/6th of that.
I did not adhere to any strategy -I picked random numbers
Best strategy would be picking the same number for all rounds. I did not use the strategy
The best strategy for choosing a number would be to choose the highest number, and stick with that number.
just choose 6
I just chose the same number each time
Just choose 6 every time
Choosing 6 is the best strategy because, since it is a fair dice, there is a 1 in 6 chance for each number. Since you lose 0 quarters if you correctly bet and get 6, that is the best strategy.
I think the best strategy was to choose whichever number came first in your mind. I didn't change my strategy and left it to luck to decide whether I get the number or not.
At first each number seems to have equal possibility. However as the thing progresses some numbers evidently have larger possibilities.
Observing the numbers that came up most frequently (I know that the way I throw the dice influences the result).
Every round go for a six
just choose randomly.
I just chose 6 every time. Logically there was a chance that it would land on the 6 at least one of the ten times. (It did, finally.)
best is to choose 6, because you would keep all quarters
Random guesses until the dice had been rolled 6 times, then the number which had appeared the least often
Choose one number and stay with it for the entire game-- I didn't think to use that strategy until midway during the experiment
The best strategy is to choose 6 for each throw. I chose 4 for one round based on a gut reaction, but it was a poor choice.
